This article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama, recognizing and celebrating the 150th anniversary of the unification of Italy as a single state. The proclamation acknowledges the courage, sacrifice, and vision of the patriots who contributed to the birth of the Italian nation. It also highlights the influence of Giuseppe Garibaldi's campaign for Italian unification, which inspired people around the world, including the 39th New York Infantry. The proclamation emphasizes the strong friendship and shared values between Italy and the United States, such as civil liberties, democratic principles, and universal human rights. President Obama encourages all Americans to learn more about the history of Italian unification and to honor the enduring friendship between the two countries.